'''Oregon, Pacific & Eastern 19,''' also known as OP&E 19, is a preserved {{whyte|2-8-2}} "Mikado" type [[steam locomotive]], built in April 1915 by the [[Baldwin Locomotive Works]] (BLW) for the [[Caddo and Choctaw Railroad]] (C&CRR) in Arkansas. The locomotive also operated for the United States Smelting, Refining and Mining Company (USSR&MC), [[McCloud River Railroad]] (MCR), [[Yreka Western Railroad]] (YW), and the [[Oregon, Pacific and Eastern Railway|Oregon, Pacific, and Eastern Railway]] (OPE). The engine operated in Mexico before being sold to the [[McCloud River Railroad]] and then to the [[Yreka Western Railroad]], before being moved up to [[Cottage Grove, Oregon]] to run on the OP&E in excursion service.<ref name=":0"/><ref name="Locomotive 19"/> In the late 1980s, No. 19 was sent back down to [[Yreka, California]] to run on the YW after the financial collapse of the OP&E. In April 1994, the engine returned to [[McCloud, California]] to run a series of excursions on the [[McCloud Railway]].<ref name="Locomotive 19"/> It has since been used in the films ''[[Emperor of the North Pole]]'' and ''[[Stand by Me (film)|Stand By Me]]''.<ref name=":0"/><ref name="Locomotive 19"/> As of 2026, No. 19 is operational at the [[Age of Steam Roundhouse]] in [[Sugarcreek, Ohio]].<ref name=":0"/><ref name="Locomotive 19"/>
In 2020, restoration officially began to return the engine to operating condition.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hayhurst |first=Leonard L.|title=All aboard for the Age of Steam Roundhouse |url=https://www.coshoctontribune.com/story/news/local/2020/08/23/all-aboard-age-steam-roundhouse/3401830001/|access-date=2022-11-09 |website=Coshocton Tribune |language=en-US}}</ref><ref name="Trains.com2"/> On October 11, 2025, it was confirmed that No. 19's restoration is near completion and it was announced that No. 19 will return to steam on April 9, 2026 for a three day grand steam christening event.<ref name="Trains.com2">{{Cite web |author=Trains Staff |title=Age of Steam Roundhouse’s 2-8-2 No. 19 to receive christening in April |url=https://www.trains.com/trn/railroads/heritage-rail/preservation/age-of-steam-roundhouses-2-8-2-no-19-to-receive-christening-in-april/ |date=October 11, 2025 |access-date=October 13, 2025 |website=Trains.com |language=en-US}}</ref> On March 16th, 2026, No. 19, now relettered to its Oregon, Pacific & Eastern livery, had a test run just outside of [[Sugarcreek, Ohio]] on the [[Ohio Central Railroad System]]. The engine was repainted to its OP&E livery because of the orig

diff_added:
| election_name = 1884 United States presidential election in Nevada
{{Elections in Nevada sidebar}}
This is one of only three elections as of [[2024 United States presidential election in Nevada|2024]] where a Democrat won the presidency without carrying Nevada (the other instances were [[1892 United States presidential election|eight years later]] when Grover Cleveland won a second, non consecutive term as [[Populist Party (United States)|Populist]] [[James B. Weaver]] [[1892 United States presidential election in Nevada|carried Nevada]], and [[1976 United States presidential election|1976]], when [[Jimmy Carter]] [[1976 United States presidential election in Nevada|won a narrow victory]]). Nevada has been a bellwether state for most of American history, and thus this is one of only eight total elections where Nevada has voted for a losing candidate out of the forty times Nevada has voted in presidential elections. The others are the aforementioned 1892 and 1976, along with Democrat [[Winfield Scott Hancock]]'s victory four years prior in [[1880 United States presidential election|1880]]; all three of Populist Democrat [[William Jennings Bryan]]'s three runs in [[1896 United States presidential election|1896]], [[1900 United States presidential election|1900]], and [[1908 United States presidential election|1908]]; and [[Hillary Clinton]]'s victory in [[2016 United States presidential election|2016]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Historical U.S. Presidential Elections 1789-2020 - 270toWin |url=https://www.270towin.com/historical-presidential-elections/ |access-date=2022-04-27 |website=270toWin.com}}</ref>
====Counties that flipped from Democratic to Republican====
* [[United States presidential elections in Nevada]]
{{Notelist}}
{{Reflist}}

