| election_name = 1884 [[United States presidential election]] in Nevada
{{ElectionsNV}}
This is one of only three elections as of 2020 where a Democrat won the presidency without carrying Nevada (the other instances were [[1892 United States presidential election|eight years later]] when Grover Cleveland won a second, non consecutive term as [[Populist Party (United States)|Populist]] [[James B. Weaver|James Weaver]] carried Nevada, and [[1976 United States presidential election|1976]], when [[Jimmy Carter]] won a narrow victory). Nevada has been a bellwether state for most of American history, and thus this is one of only eight total elections where Nevada has voted for a losing candidate out of the forty times Nevada has voted in presidential elections. The others are the aforementioned 1892 and 1976, along with Democrat [[Winfield Scott Hancock|Winfield Scott Hancock's]] victory four years prior in [[1880 United States presidential election|1880]]; all three of Populist Democrat [[William Jennings Bryan]]'s three runs in [[1896 United States presidential election|1896]], [[1900 United States presidential election|1900]], and [[1908 United States presidential election|1908]]; and [[Hillary Clinton]]'s victory in [[2016 United States presidential election|2016]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Historical U.S. Presidential Elections 1789-2020 - 270toWin |url=https://www.270towin.com/historical-presidential-elections/ |access-date=2022-04-27 |website=270toWin.com}}</ref>
